{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":19324,"name":"","username":"JTippetts","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jtippetts/{size}/357_2.png","created_at":"2017-07-08T05:08:08.311Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWhat is the general workflow for creating UI widgets in the editor that incorporate ScrollView? I can‚Äôt, for the life of me, figure out how to create the scroll bars and content element. I‚Äôve got this widget:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"//cdck-file-uploads-global.s3.dualstack.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/3a184413828e6435f550b74de30a53d65a660591.png\" width=\"325\" height=\"500\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôve been building it by hand but I‚Äôm trying to figure out how to build such a beast in the editor instead, for quicker iteration on designs. However, I can‚Äôt figure out how to set up the content and scroll bars. For my own edification, I tried saving the widget to XML after creating it by hand, but importing the saved XML into the editor doesn‚Äôt work well. The widget imports (sort of; the icons for the scroll arrows and scrollbar field are screwed up and there are other issues as well), and it has scroll bars and a content pane (albeit with the screwed up icons), but I can‚Äôt access those internal elements via the edit tree. They appear on the widget, but I can‚Äôt edit them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôm guessing that I need to create the widget in different pieces: the frame/box with the selector buttons and a panel for the scrollview widget, then manually set up the scroll view and scroll bars and add them to the panel. This seems kinda clunky to me. Am I missing something?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-07-08T05:08:18.895Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":52,"reads":49,"readers_count":48,"score":269.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":3331,"topic_slug":"creating-scrollview-widgets-in-the-editor","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":30,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19326,"name":"","username":"Mike","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/58f4c7/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-07-08T06:32:06.725Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI don‚Äôt think you can fully build the ScrollView in the Editor, as it expects a content UIElement, not a child.\u003cbr\u003e\nThe easiest workflow is to build the Window and the ScrollView content (for example a Window with your rows) in the Editor.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThen in code:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eUIElement@ window = ui.LoadLayout(cache.GetResource(\"XMLFile\", \"UI/MyWindow.xml\"));\nScrollView@ scrollView = window.CreateChild(\"ScrollView\");\nscrollView.SetStyleAuto();\nscrollView.autoDisableChildren = true;\nscrollView.SetScrollBarsVisible(false, true);\nUIElement@ content = ui.LoadLayout(cache.GetResource(\"XMLFile\", \"UI/MyContent.xml\"));\nscrollView.contentElement = content;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eScroll bars visibility is controlled by SetScrollBarsVisible()\u003cbr\u003e\n‚ÄòMyContent.xml‚Äô is your SrollView content. It can be any UIElement.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou end up with this hierarchy:\u003cbr\u003e\nWindow (the main layout) \u0026gt; ScrollView (from code) \u0026gt; Window2 (content)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNote that you will certainly have to tweak size and alignment to get the expected display.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"201